(64, 0, 'Writing Workshops and Close Reading in the Inquiry Classroom with Kathy Collins', '<table id="subheader_table">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td id="subheader_info_cell">\r\n<div id="event_header">\r\n<h1>Writing Workshops and Close Reading in the Inquiry Classroom with Kathy Collins</h1>\r\n<h2><a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/o/international-school-manila-8396873528" target="_blank">International School Manila</a></h2>\r\n<h2>Saturday, January 30, 2016 at 8:00 AM-Sunday, January 31, 2016 at 3:30 PM (PHT)</h2>\r\n<div id="event_network">\r\n<h2><a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/d/philippines--taguig/events/">Taguig, Philippines</a></h2>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Event Details</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Writing Workshops and Close Reading in the Inquiry Classroom</p>\r\n<p>Workshop Overview:</p>\r\n<p>For a great many teachers, an underlying tension can arise when we strive to be well-planned, yet we also want to infuse a writing workshop model with an inquiry-mindset. On one hand, teachers may appreciate the instructional security of pre-planned units of study to help guide their day-to-day teaching, yet on the other hand, they resist instruction that feels scripted, mandated, and meant for classrooms elsewhere. How, then, might we create conditions within our workshops so that children learn all they need to know to become engaged, strategic writers, while also making room for them to pursue questions, projects, and interests that may arise?</p>\r\n<p>In addition, when reading with our students, how do we work with them to slow down, linger, study, and ask questions to dig into the text. Children who learn this stance of looking, lingering and wondering about the choices the author or illustrator have made are practicing skills that will evolve intothe Close Readingthat our upper grade colleagues are talking about. It is important of elementary teachers to lay this groundwork in a developmentally appropriate and meaningful way.</p>\r\n<p>Day 1of this workshop is designed for teachers who are developing writing workshops in their classrooms but who also want to be sure to infuse childrens experiences as writers with a spirit of inquiry and unforeseen possibilities.</p>\r\n<p>Day 2will continue this work, but will also include time for developing mini-lessons around Close Reading that can be used in your Reading Workshops.</p>\r\n<p>With the support of activities, demonstrations, and video, elementary grade teachers consider these questions:</p>\r\n<p> How do we implement writing workshops characterized by equal parts intention and joy?</p>\r\n<p> What are research-based best practices for effective whole-group, small group, and one-to-one instruction?</p>\r\n<p> How can we fit an inquiry mindset into our writing curricula and balanced literacy components?</p>\r\n<p> How can we support children to be the kinds of readers who dig in, think deeply, grow ideas and share their thinking about books?</p>\r\n<p>This two-day workshop is full of practical ideas and classroom strategies to help teachers find the sweet spot that exists between being well-planned and being highly responsive, between a writing workshop and an inquiry-based approach to teaching and learning.</p>\r\n<p>The days will be divided into these portions:</p>\r\n<p>1) A wide-angled look at a comprehensive literacy approach that issues invitations to all learners</p>\r\n<p>2) A zoomed-in examination of best practices within workshop teaching</p>\r\n<p>3) A close-up on ways to open the workshop up for inquiry-based teaching and learning</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div dir="ltr">\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Have questions about Writing Workshops and Close Reading in the Inquiry Classroom with Kathy Collins?<a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/e/writing-workshops-and-close-reading-in-the-inquiry-classroom-with-kathy-collins-tickets-19141034349?aff=ehomecard#lightbox_contact" data-organizer-id="8396873528" data-event-id="19141034349" data-xd-wired="modal">Contact International School Manila</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 100, 'Writing_Workshops_and_Close_Reading_in_the_Inquiry_Classroom_with_Kathy_Collins', 1, 2, 1449547420, 0, 0, 0, 11, 'main', 0, 0, 'Writing_Workshops_and_Close_Reading_in_the_Inquiry_Classroom_with_Kathy_Collins', '0.000', 'and,that,writing,inquiry,workshops,for,workshop,teachers', 'kg', 1449569373, 'For a great many teachers, an underlying tension can arise when we strive to be well-planned, yet we also want to infuse a writing workshop model with an inquiry-mindset. On one hand, teachers may appreciate the instructional security of pre-planned units', 'm', '0.000', '0.000', '0.000', 0, 'all', '', 0, 0, 0, 1449569393, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 'Writing Workshops and Close Reading in the Inquiry Classroom with Kathy Collins', 'writing-workshops-and-close-reading-in-the-inquiry-classroom-with-kathy-collins', '0.0000000', '0.0000000', '', 0, ''),
(65, 0, 'Dante Alighieri Today', '<header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/dante-alighieri-today-tickets-19355236032?aff=ebrowse#listing-organizer" data-d-duration="1500" data-d-offset="0" data-d-destination="#listing-organizer" data-xd-wired="scroll-to">By: Societ Dante Alighieri di Manila</a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>Event Description</h2>\r\n<div data-xd-wired="read-more">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>This year, we celebrate the 750th anniversary of the birth of Dante Alighieri, considered the father of the Italian language and one of the greatest poets in the whole world.<br />For this reason we would like to offer you a month long journey into the work of Dante Alighieri, a series of events that will highlight the relevance of his work in our contemporary world. The contemporaneity of Dante and the Divine Comedy will be explored through many art disciplines and events. It will focus on three particular perspectives: Dante and the world literature, Dante Today in Italy and Dante Today in the Philippines.</p>\r\n<p>Conferences and Lectures<br />Italian thematic dinners<br />Illustration exhibit on the Divine Comedy<br />Reading of theDivine Comedy and performances<br />Interactive paint exhibit<br />Choral performance<br />Poster activities<br />Short animation film competition<br />Video installation<br />Movie showing projection<br />Workshops on teaching Dante Alighieri</p>\r\n<p>The cycle of events will take place starting in the second half of October 2015 and will run for the entire month of November.<br />Dante Alighieris works influenced cultures, arts and popular views and opinions all over the world.<br />Countless literary works in Italy and abroad were based or cited the work of Dante Alighieri, more than 50 movies and 50 musical pieces, were created after the Divine Comedy and its messages. In the popular culture, games, comics and various animations were inspired by Dante Alighieri.<br />The Societa Dante Alighieri, with more than 400 branches all over the world was established in 1889 with the aim to disseminate the Italian language and culture in the world, and is one with the whole world to organize initiatives to celebrate Dante Alighieri and his work.</p>\r\n<p><br />In line with this, the tSocieta Dante Alighieri Comitato di Manila, wiith the Embassy of Italy in Manila,<a href="https://www.facebook.com/ItalianChamberPH/" rel="nofollow">The Italian Chamber of Commerce in the Philippines</a>,<a href="https://www.facebook.com/philippineitalianassociation/" rel="nofollow">The Philippine Italian Association</a>together with other partners would like to celebrate Dante Alighieri in ways that would encourage more and more Filipinos to appreciate his work and relevance in modern times!</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>https://www.facebook.com/events/884732914908416/</p>\r\n<p>http://protees.ph/DanteAlighieri</p>\r\n<p>https://www.facebook.com/Societ%C3%A0-Dante-Alighieri-Manila-654457484667474/events</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<dl>\r\n<dt data-automation="listing-info-language">WHEN</dt>\r\n<dd><time data-automation="event-details-time">Tuesday, November 3, 2015 at 7:00 PM-Wednesday, December 16, 2015 at 10:00 PM (PHT)-<a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/dante-alighieri-today-tickets-19355236032?aff=ebrowse#add-to-calendar-modal" data-automation="add-to-calendar" data-xd-wired="modal">Add to Calendar</a></time></dd>\r\n<dt>WHERE</dt>\r\n<dd>Metro Manila - , NCR PH -<a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/dante-alighieri-today-tickets-19355236032?aff=ebrowse#map-target" data-d-duration="1500" data-d-offset="-85" data-d-destination="#map-target" data-xd-wired="scroll-to">View Map</a></dd>\r\n<dt data-automation="ListingsBreadcrumbsTitle">TAGS</dt>\r\n<dd data-automation="ListingsBreadcrumbs">\r\n<section><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/d/local/festivals/" data-event-action="BreadcrumbFormat" data-event-catego