(75, 0, 'Storytelling as a Facilitation Technology', '<header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/storytelling-as-a-facilitation-technology-tickets-19437351642?aff=ebrowse#listing-organizer" data-d-duration="1500" data-d-offset="0" data-d-destination="#listing-organizer" data-xd-wired="scroll-to">By: IAF Philippines</a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>Event Description</h2>\r\n<div data-xd-wired="read-more">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>We all know that stories entertain and engage us. We also know that stories put across lessons and help us create and sustain valuean be used for individuals and organizations.</p>\r\n<p>Most all of us employ stories to communicate our experiences and our expectations.</p>\r\n<p>In a professional setting where leaders/facilitators need to churn up energies and gather and move them towards a constructive goal the gentle art of storytelling can be powerfully and effectively used. Though the discipline of facilitation is a process rather than content creation or sharing, storytelling can employed to evoke stories, unleash visions and inspire action.</p>\r\n<p>In this learnings session by IAF Philippines we invite you come and learn the science behind the art of storytelling thus making it a facilitation technology.</p>\r\n<p>You will learn...</p>\r\n<p>- what makes a good story</p>\r\n<p>- where to source stories</p>\r\n<p>- how to structure stories</p>\r\n<p>- how to tell stories gently and creatively</p>\r\n<p>- how to tell stories so others share their stories</p>\r\n<p>- how to generate and evoke more stories</p>\r\n<p>- how to facilitate positive outcomes</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>The session will be interactive, safe and fun.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<dl>\r\n<dt data-automation="listing-info-language">WHEN</dt>\r\n<dd><time data-automation="event-details-time">Saturday, January 23, 2016 from 3:30 PM to 6:30 PM (PHT)-<a 